## 4. The Hand Feel Experience

- Impact Sensation
    - Hardness Words: Feels medium-hard. Though the sponge is officially 40 degrees (Butterfly scale, ~50 ESN), the widely spaced pimples make it feel softer and more accessible than D05.
    - Feedback: Crisp and sharp.
    - Hold vs. Release: Very fast release. It bites just enough to grip, then shoots the ball out instantly.
    - Dwell Time: Short to medium. Much less dwell time than D05 or D09c.

- Sound/Click
    - Produces a satisfying, sharp crack when hit flat, though slightly less metallic than classic ESN rubbers.

