## 5. Compatibility & Setup Guide

- Best Blade Matches
    - Outer Carbon: (e.g., Viscaria, Timo Boll ALC) Creates an absolute speed weapon for off-the-bounce attackers. Requires high skill to control.
    - Inner Carbon: (e.g., Innerforce Layer ALC/ZLC) Highly recommended. The blade provides the dwell time and control that the rubber lacks, balancing the setup perfectly.
    - All-Wood: (e.g., Korbel) A great match for players who want the speed of Dignics but need the supreme feedback of a 5-ply wood blade.
    - Mismatch Cases: Ultra-fast, stiff carbon blades (e.g., Sardius, Primorac Carbon) make this rubber dangerously uncontrollable for anyone below pro-level.

- Forehand vs. Backhand Recommendation
    - Forehand: Great for players who stand a step back from the table and prefer drive-looping or smashing over brush-looping.
    - Backhand: The ideal placement for many. Perfect for players who rely on punch blocks, fast flat hits, and direct backhand drives.

